BASIC YELLOW CAKE

2 3/4 c all-purpose flour	1 3/4 c sugar
2 1/2 tsp baking powder		1 1/2 tsp vanilla
1 tsp salt			2 eggs
1/2 c butter or margarine	1 1/4 c milk

Grease and lightly flour two 9-inch round cake pans.  Combine flour,
baking powder, and salt.  Beat butter about 30 seconds.  Add sugar and
vanilla; beat until well combined.  Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1
minute after each.  Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, beating
after each addition.  Turn into pans.  Bake at 375 for 30 to 35
minutes or until cake tests done.  Cool 10 minutes in pans.  Remove
from pans and cool on wire racks.
